# This file contains serial numbers for all Spin5 boards. Each board has

# The Manufacture ID is on a small label on the PCB and was put there by
# Norcott at manufacture time. It is a 5 character ID and is the first
# item on each line. The encoding is not known but all IDs to date are
# an asterisk followed by 4 upper-case alphanumerics. The letters I and
# O are not used.
#
# The BMP ID is a 128-bit number which is stored in the BMP and
# retrieved by software. Again the encoding is not known. This is the
# second item on each line and will be absent for boards which have not yet
# been configured. We have been retrieving these numbers as each
# board is configured and placing them in this file by manual copy (so
# there could be mistakes). Some boards fail to load or run the BMP
# firmware so it's not possible to get their BMP IDs. In this case an ID
# of the form
#
#     ffffffff-ffffffff-ffffffff-0000nnnn
#
# has been manually allocated. There is one board (*6Q2V) whose BMP ID
